{
  "texts": [
    "In reality, no company can operate in isolation, and it forms a broader network of suppliers, customers, competitors, and business partners.",
    "Events that influence one company can also have an impact on others within the network, which can be used to predict the stock price.",
    "However, traditional sentiment-based approaches typically consider only the sentiment of the target company [10].",
    "Furthermore, effective capture of inter-company sentiment relationships remains a critical challenge in the field.Furthermore, incorporating sentiment analysis into stock price prediction models can significantly improve the precision of prediction [11][12][13].",
    "However, effectively leveraging news sentiment poses challenges, particularly when there is minimal news coverage about target companies, as is often the case with stocks that have low trading volumes."
  ]
}